### Discography

Miranda's discography is extensive, featuring cast albums, soundtrack albums, and mixtapes. His cast albums include those for *[In the Heights](/In_the_Heights)*, *[Merrily We Roll Along](/Merrily_We_Roll_Along_(musical))* (Encores! Cast), *[Bring It On: The Musical](/Bring_It_On:_The_Musical)*, *[21 Chump Street](/21_Chump_Street)*, and the monumental *[Hamilton](/Hamilton_(album))* which achieved Diamond certification from the [RIAA](/Recording_Industry_Association_of_America).

Soundtrack albums include the successful *[Moana](/Moana_(soundtrack))*, *[Mary Poppins Returns](/Mary_Poppins_Returns_(soundtrack))*, *[In the Heights](/In_the_Heights_(soundtrack))*, *[Vivo](/Vivo_(film))*, *[Encanto](/Encanto_(soundtrack))*, *[The Little Mermaid](/The_Little_Mermaid_(2023_soundtrack))*, and *[Mufasa: The Lion King](/Mufasa:_The_Lion_King_(soundtrack))*. His soundtrack mixtapes and concept albums include *[The Hamilton Mixtape](/The_Hamilton_Mixtape)* and *[Warriors](/Warriors_(Lin-Manuel_Miranda_and_Eisa_Davis_album))*.

Notable singles include "Jabba Flow" with [John Williams](/John_Williams), "[Love Make the World Go Round](/Love_Make_the_World_Go_Round)" with [Jennifer Lopez](/Jennifer_Lopez), "[Almost Like Praying](/Almost_Like_Praying)" with Artists for Puerto Rico, "[Found/Tonight](/Found/Tonight)" with [Ben Platt](/Ben_Platt_(actor)), and songs from *Moana* such as "We Know the Way" and "You're Welcome." He also contributed "[Dos Oruguitas](/Dos_Oruguitas)" to the *[Encanto](/Encanto)* soundtrack, for which he received an [Academy Award](/Academy_Awards) nomination.

### Bibliography

Miranda has authored several books, including *Hamilton: The Revolution* (2016) with Jeremy McCarter, *Gmorning, Gnight!: Little Pep Talks for Me & You* (2018) with [Jonny Sun](/Jonny_Sun), and *In the Heights: Finding Home* (2021) with [Quiara Alegría Hudes](/Quiara_Alegr%C3%ADa_Hudes) and Jeremy McCarter. He has also contributed opinion pieces to *[The New York Times](/The_New_York_Times)*, such as "Stop the Bots from Killing Broadway" (2016) and "Give Puerto Rico Its Chance to Thrive" (2016).

